From: =?utf-8?b?T3R0byBLZWvDpGzDpGluZW4=?= <otto@debian.org>
Date: Sat, 28 Dec 2024 15:45:58 -0800
Subject: Update test to be compatible with latest Glamour v0.8.0

Latest src:golang-github-charmbracelet-glamour 0.8.0-1 caused the tests
in dh-make-golang to fail to due slightly changed line wrapping. Fix
this by updating the tests to match the new expected output.

Also update the dependencies so that Glamour is v0.8.0 and everything else
has the bare minimal update as generated by `go mod tidy`.

Closes: Debian Bug#1091273
---
 description_test.go | 8 ++++----
 go.mod              | 2 +-
 2 files changed, 5 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/description_test.go b/description_test.go
index 12acec9..97b10c9 100644
--- a/description_test.go
+++ b/description_test.go
@@ -85,10 +85,10 @@ the command-line.
  .
   1. Call glamour.Render(inputText, "desiredStyle")
   2. Set the GLAMOUR_STYLE environment variable to your desired default
-     style or a file location for a style and call
-     glamour.RenderWithEnvironmentConfig(inputText)
-  3. Set the GLAMOUR_STYLE environment variable and pass
-     glamour.WithEnvironmentConfig() to your custom renderer
+     style or a file location for a style and call glamour.
+     RenderWithEnvironmentConfig(inputText)
+  3. Set the GLAMOUR_STYLE environment variable and pass glamour.
+     WithEnvironmentConfig() to your custom renderer
  .
  Glamourous Projects
  .
diff --git a/go.mod b/go.mod
index 5affdb3..a0e44d7 100644
--- a/go.mod
+++ b/go.mod
@@ -5,7 +5,7 @@ go 1.21
 toolchain go1.22.1
 
 require (
-	github.com/charmbracelet/glamour v0.3.1-0.20211129115518-6db32e77e152
+	github.com/charmbracelet/glamour v0.8.0
